{
  "stem": "25288.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I had a four elementary school and four-year high school.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And, of course, in the Hebrew school.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After the bar mitzvah, usually the higher education was to go to [INAUDIBLE] yeshiva.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But my father needed me in the store.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So it wasn't-- there was a yeshiva in Tokaj.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But that time we didn't have a yeshiva because the rabbi passed away a year before and we didn't have a new rabbi.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What we we had are dayan.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know what a dayan is?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Rabbi-- actually, dayan means a judge.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was also a rabbi.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Not assistant, but a second rabbi.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And over there I went and studied privately maybe a year or two year.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I didn't-- I really didn't like it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Somehow I didn't like it, so I quit about two years.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then I was working full in the store.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a Jewish school, yeah.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So everybody religious had the separate elementary school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Jewish congregation had their own school.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Catholic congregation had their own school.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there were the [INAUDIBLE] and Methodists.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there were several schools, the elementary school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Then the high school was public.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That was public.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But my father-- we were very religious, so my mother didn't let me go to the public school because we have to go over there on Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So that's why I took the high school private.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There were several Jewish kids who were privately.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In the cheder, in the Hebrew school, Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It wasn't allowed to speak other language, only Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that's how I learned.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My parents, together, most of the time, they spoke German.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because my father came from a district of Hungary where people mostly were speaking German, and also my mother.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
